def make_good(s: str) -> str:
    result = []
    for c in s:
        if result and abs(ord(result[-1]) - ord(c)) == 32:
            result.pop()
        else:
            result.append(c)
    return "".join(result)
```


    The algorithm iterates through the input string. For each character, it checks whether the last character in the result string has the same letter but different case (i.e., the ASCII distance between the two characters is 32). If so, it removes the last character from the result string. Otherwise, it appends the current character to the result string. The final result is then returned.

